From: vyos-ls1046a-build CI <ci@local>
Date: Mon, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: export OOT CC-target resolvers
 (dpaa_get_rx_fman_port/dpaa_get_tx_fqid)

Single-image Gap-A prerequisite for repointing the out-of-tree ASK2 PCD
consumer (ask.ko) onto the common board fman_cc_*/fman_hm_* substrate.
The rebuild-via-install per-flow model (mirroring the productive 0109
ethtool-ntuple CC bridge) needs two net_device -> hardware-id resolvers
that exist today only in the dead ask-flavor patches 0031/0039 (which
patch the nonexistent-in-common <linux/fsl/dpaa_flow_offload.h>).  Provide
them on the common substrate instead:

  * dpaa_get_rx_fman_port(dev) -> the ingress RX struct fman_port, fed to
    fman_port_get_id() to derive the BMI hard port id used as the
    fman_cc_tree_install/destroy port key (the same key 0104/0109 use).
  * dpaa_get_tx_fqid(dev, queue, *fqid) -> the egress TX QMan FQID used as
    a CC key target_fqid for FORWARD_FQ[_WITH_MANIP].

Both are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL, NULL/non-dpaa-safe, and dormant in-tree (no
caller yet; ask.ko consumes them once the oot-ungate lands).  Bodies are
the proven 0031/0039 definitions reparented from dpaa_flow_offload.h onto
the dpaa_fman_caps.h substrate already #included by dpaa_eth.c (0086), so
the prototypes satisfy -Wmissing-prototypes at the definition site.
fman_port_use_kg_hash() is NOT re-exported here -- it is already exported
in the common series by board patch 0105.

Spec: specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 13.4/13.5.

Signed-off-by: vyos-ls1046a-build CI <ci@local>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -4350,6 +4350,56 @@
 	.remove = dpaa_remove
 };
 
+/*
+ * dpaa_get_rx_fman_port() / dpaa_get_tx_fqid() (board patch 0121)
+ *
+ * OOT CC-target resolvers for the single-image ASK2 PCD consumer (ask.ko).
+ * They turn a kernel net_device into the DPAA1 hardware identifiers a
+ * static CC tree needs: the ingress RX struct fman_port (feed to
+ * fman_port_get_id() for the fman_cc_tree_* port key) and an egress TX
+ * frame-queue id (the target_fqid a CC FORWARD_FQ[_WITH_MANIP] action
+ * enqueues to).  Both validate the device is dpaa-owned before touching
+ * private state.  Bodies mirror the dead ask-flavor exports 0039/0031 but
+ * are reparented onto the common dpaa_fman_caps.h substrate.  Callers hold
+ * RTNL (or equivalent) so the dpaa_priv cannot be freed underneath them.
+ */
+struct fman_port *dpaa_get_rx_fman_port(struct net_device *dev)
+{
+	struct dpaa_priv *priv;
+
+	if (!dev)
+		return NULL;
+	if (dev->netdev_ops != &dpaa_ops)
+		return NULL;
+	priv = netdev_priv(dev);
+	if (!priv->mac_dev)
+		return NULL;
+	return priv->mac_dev->port[RX];
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(dpaa_get_rx_fman_port);
+
+int dpaa_get_tx_fqid(struct net_device *dev, u32 queue, u32 *fqid)
+{
+	struct dpaa_priv *priv;
+
+	if (!dev || !fqid)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	if (dev->netdev_ops != &dpaa_ops)
+		return -ENODEV;
+
+	if (queue >= dpaa_max_num_txqs())
+		return -ERANGE;
+
+	priv = netdev_priv(dev);
+	if (!priv->egress_fqs || !priv->egress_fqs[queue])
+		return -ENOENT;
+
+	*fqid = qman_fq_fqid(priv->egress_fqs[queue]);
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(dpaa_get_tx_fqid);
+
 static int __init dpaa_load(void)
 {
 	int err;
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
@@ -381,6 +381,39 @@
  */
 int  fman_hm_nexthop_put(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id, u32 handle);
 
+/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ *
+ * OOT CC-target resolvers (board patch 0121)
+ *
+ * Helpers an out-of-tree PCD consumer (ask.ko) uses to turn a kernel
+ * net_device into the DPAA1 hardware identifiers a static CC tree needs:
+ * the ingress RX fman_port (-> fman_port_get_id() -> port_id key) and an
+ * egress TX frame-queue id (-> fman_cc_key.target_fqid).  Both validate
+ * that the device is DPAA-owned before dereferencing private state.
+ * ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
+struct net_device;
+struct fman_port;
+
+/**
+ * dpaa_get_rx_fman_port - ingress RX fman_port backing a DPAA netdev
+ * @dev: a DPAA-owned net_device
+ *
+ * Returns the RX-side struct fman_port, or NULL when @dev is not a DPAA
+ * interface or has no bound MAC.  Feed the result to fman_port_get_id()
+ * to obtain the BMI hard port id used as the fman_cc_tree_* port key.
+ */
+struct fman_port *dpaa_get_rx_fman_port(struct net_device *dev);
+
+/**
+ * dpaa_get_tx_fqid - egress TX frame-queue id for a DPAA netdev
+ * @dev:   a DPAA-owned net_device (the flow's sink/egress interface)
+ * @queue: egress queue index (< dpaa_max_num_txqs())
+ * @fqid:  out; receives the QMan FQID on success
+ *
+ * Returns 0 and writes @fqid, or -EINVAL/-ENODEV/-ERANGE/-ENOENT.  The
+ * FQID is the target_fqid a CC FORWARD_FQ[_WITH_MANIP] action enqueues to.
+ */
+int dpaa_get_tx_fqid(struct net_device *dev, u32 queue, u32 *fqid);
+
 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ *
  * M3-3d STUB API  (spec sec 5.6 Policer)
